    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This is because pandas formatter uses major and minor labels with different internal location from python datetime.\r\n\r\n```\r\nax = pd.Series(range(10), idx).plot()\r\n[str(x) for x in ax.get_xticklabels()]\r\n# [\"Text(540,0,'Jan\\\\n2015')\"]\r\n[str(x) for x in ax.get_xticklabels(minor=True)]\r\n# [\"Text(540,0,'')\", \"Text(541,0,'Feb')\", \"Text(542,0,'Mar')\", \"Text(543,0,'Apr')\", \"Text(544,0,'May')\", \"Text(545,0,'Jun')\", \"Text(546,0,'Jul')\", \"Text(547,0,'Aug')\", \"Text(548,0,'Sep')\", \"Text(549,0,'Oct')\"]\r\n````\r\n\r\nYou can do:\r\n\r\n```\r\nax = pd.Series(range(10), idx).plot()\r\nax.set_xticks([539 + i for i in range(1, 10, 2)])\r\nax.set_xticklabels(['2015-{}'.format(i) for i in range(1, 10, 2)])\r\nax.minorticks_off()\r\n```"
  },
